title: God of Thunder indeed!
body: So, I’m sitting watching Avengers: Infinity War again in anticipation of going to see End Game tomorrow. It’s the big battle and Thor just made that awesome entrance…. Then there’s a big clap of thunder and lightning *outside*, for real and the lights dim for a second. Talk about timing! I feel like I’ve been blessed somehow.

blog.description: She/Her, 20, Ace, french art studient, hufflepuff and multifandom. Enjoy !

title: Cryogenics
body:
Fandom : Marvel

In English, by Sodafly, Rated E

Synopsis : “What is there to know?” Bucky asks although he knows the answer, leaning into the gentle touch. Gentleness is something so unfamiliar. 
“You.” 
“We’re the same Steve. We’re the Winter Soldier.” 
“Then why do I call you Bucky and why do you call me Steve?” 
-
AU where both Steve and Bucky fall from the train and become the Winter Soldiers

Pairing : Steve Rogers/Bucky Barnes

1 chapter, Complete -> here 

Why do I recommend it : Because I really liked this version of Winter Soldiers!Steve and Bucky. Without their past and memories, the two men are still profoundly linked, to the point of having a single identity. They are the Winter Soldier, a person torn in two parts. They’re confused, not understanding their need to be with each other, totally controlled by Hydra.

The resulting story is harsh, heartbreaking, describing their life as a weapon made to celebrate the Soviets and Hydra. Are they really alive? Or just shells of the men who fell from the train in Austria?

summary: I can't believe Avengers: Endgame is basically three hours of the Avengers just eating some shawarma. Well, it is, but then...
body: I can’t believe Avengers: Endgame is basically three hours of the Avengers just eating some shawarma. Well, it is, but then Deadpool shows up and wants some of that shawarma but the Avengers won’t let him have any of their special shawarma. So Deadpool challenges all of them to a rap battle. Most of the Avengers didn’t even made it to the final round. Only Steve Rogers and Tony Stark did and they sure know how to spit some wicked beats. And when it was time for the winner to be announced, the screen went blank. That wasn’t even fair! I’m totally wrecked by that movie.
